'Bolter' (crossbow with some kind of special ability)\par
*What sort of vague ability?*\par
Similar to a regular crossbow, the Bolter is a wonder of tinkering and engineering. Employing a unique loading mechanism, each firing cocks the crossbow again, letting the a box of bolts be mounted so that the user can fire repeatedly.\par
\par
'Knives of Knal' (these are throwing knives, maybe they are fashioned from huge teeth?)\par
The city of Knal is famed for its arena, and the corpses of slain monsters are often recycled into weapons or armor for the gladiators. Fashioned from the teeth of a particularly large and vicious reptile, these knives seem to unerringly seek the nearest flesh when thrown.\par
\par
Shuriken Stars\par
The Shuriken are proof that not all weapons need to be large to be deadly. Small and easily concealed, they will often be used by warriors to put an opponent off guard, resulting in his distraction and subsequent death.\par
\par
Improved Mace (why is it improved? I don't know...)\par
Maces can be simple in construction, with just a wooden shaft and a metal head. The improved mace is made of the best materials that can be afforded, consisting of a steel flanged head mounted on a steel shaft and capable of taking as much punishment as it can deal.\par
\par
Staff of Light (a melee weapon that improves the magician's arcane ranged attack)\par
Similar to a normal staff only in nature, the Staff of Light has a golden glow that does not dim even at night. When a mage wields the staff in combat, the magnitude of his magical attacks are increased.\par
\par
Staff of Fire (a melee weapon that improves the magician's fire ranged attack)\par
Similar to a normal staff only in nature, the Staff of Fire is wrapped in coils of fire that flicker and flare of their own accord. In the hands of a mage, the fires will not harm his flesh, but will swell to enhance the fire he directs at his enemies.\par
\par
Staff of Ice (a melee weapon that improves the magician's cold ranged attack)\par
Similar to a normal staff only in nature, the Staff of Ice is covered in glittering ice crystals. Chill to the touch, a mage who wields this staff in combat will find his cold attacks striking with the strength of a blizzard.\par
\par
Glaive\par
A long spear with a sword blade on the end, the glaive has proven effective against both mounted and dismounted enemies. In the hands of a trained individual, both the haft and blade will be employed to keep an enemy on the defensive.\par
